---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'

const title = "Privacy Policy | Time Stones"
const description = "Learn how Time Stones protects your privacy and data. We value transparency and ensure your information stays securely on your device."
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-300" style="background: white; padding: 20px; margin: 30px 50px; border-radius: 30px;">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center text-white mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 text-center mb-10">Last Updated: November 2025</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3 text-white">1. Introduction</h2>
    <p>
      Welcome to <strong>Time Stones</strong>, a personal productivity and self-reflection app. 
      Your privacy is very important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your information when you use our mobile application.
      We believe in transparency and simplicity — the app is designed to function 
      <strong>without collecting or sharing any personal data</strong>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3 text-white">2. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>
      Time Stones does not automatically collect, transmit, or store any personal data.
      All information you enter (such as daily logs or reflections) is 
      <strong>manually entered by you</strong> and stored 
      <strong>locally on your device</strong> only.
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-3">
      <li>No personal information (name, email, contact details)</li>
      <li>No app usage or analytics data</li>
      <li>No location or device identifiers</li>
      <li>No sensitive or health data</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3 text-white">3. Data Storage</h2>
    <p>
      All data is securely stored <strong>locally on your device</strong>. 
      We do not have access to your data, and it is never uploaded to any external servers.
      If you uninstall the app, all stored data is permanently deleted.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3 text-white">4. Future Features</h2>
    <p>
      In the future, optional features such as <strong>cloud backup for premium users</strong>, 
      or <strong>analytics and ads</strong> may be introduced. When these become available, 
      this Privacy Policy will be updated to explain what data is collected, how it is used, 
      and how you can manage or opt out.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3 text-white">5. Notifications</h2>
    <p>
      Time Stones uses <strong>local notifications only</strong> to remind you about habits and reflections. 
      These notifications are generated on your device and are never transmitted externally.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3 text-white">6. Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>
      We do not share, sell, or transmit any user data to third parties.
      If analytics or advertising services are introduced in the future, 
      all third-party SDKs will comply with Google Play policies and privacy laws such as GDPR and CCPA.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3 text-white">7. Children’s Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      Time Stones is intended for <strong>general audiences</strong> and not directed toward children under 13. 
      We do not knowingly collect any personal data from children.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3 text-white">8. Data Deletion</h2>
    <p>
      Because all data is stored locally, you can delete your data by simply <strong>uninstalling the app</strong>. 
      This permanently removes all stored information.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3 text-white">9. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>
      Since no personal data is collected or stored by us, there are currently no personal data rights to exercise. 
      When cloud features are added, users will have full control to view, download, or delete their information.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3 text-white">10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy occasionally to reflect new features or legal requirements. 
      Updates will be posted at <a href="https://timestones.today" class="text-amber-400 hover:underline">timestones.today</a> 
      with the revised date shown at the top.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3 text-white">11. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>
      If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, 
      please contact us at 
      <a href="https://timestones.today" class="text-amber-400 hover:underline">timestones.today</a>.
    </p>

    <hr class="my-10 border-gray-700" />

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3 text-white">Google Play Data Safety Summary</h3>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="min-w-full border border-gray-700 text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-800 text-gray-200">
            <th class="p-2 text-left">Data Type</th>
            <th class="p-2 text-left">Collected</th>
            <th class="p-2 text-left">Shared</th>
            <th class="p-2 text-left">Stored Locally</th>
            <th class="p-2 text-left">Purpose</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-700">
          <tr>
            <td class="p-2">Personal Info</td>
            <td class="p-2">No</td>
            <td class="p-2">No</td>
            <td class="p-2">Yes</td>
            <td class="p-2">Manual user input only</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-2">App Usage</td>
            <td class="p-2">No</td>
            <td class="p-2">No</td>
            <td class="p-2">No</td>
            <td class="p-2">—</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-2">Device Data</td>
            <td class="p-2">No</td>
            <td class="p-2">No</td>
            <td class="p-2">No</td>
            <td class="p-2">—</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-2">Notifications</td>
            <td class="p-2">Yes (local only)</td>
            <td class="p-2">No</td>
            <td class="p-2">Yes</td>
            <td class="p-2">User reminders</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-2">Analytics / Ads</td>
            <td class="p-2">No (planned)</td>
            <td class="p-2">No</td>
            <td class="p-2">No</td>
            <td class="p-2">—</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
